                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The International Bank for Reconstruction and
                                        Development (IBRD) officially came into existence in 1944.
                                        It promotes economic, social, and environmental progress in
                                        developing nations by reducing poverty.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                        <Detail SortOrder="2" TypeOfProgramAndActivitiesDetailsId="2634">
                            <FooterDetails>
                                <Email/>
                                <Footer/>
                                <WebAddress>http://www.worldbank.org/en/about/what-we-do/brief/ibrd</WebAddress>
                            </FooterDetails>
                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The Bank lends funds at market-determined interest
                                        rates, provides advice, and serves as a catalyst to
                                        stimulate outside investments. Its resources come primarily
                                        from funds raised in the world capital markets, its retained
                                        earnings, and repayments on its loans.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
